csum=smectite and not kaolinite or quartz are effected by the acid activation [[https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0169131716301946|#]] A decrease in the Al2O3, MgO, Fe2O3, and Na2O contents accompanied a relative increase in SiO2. vermiculites should also work.  Actually Acid treatment of non-swelling clay minerals like illites, kaolinites or fibrous clay minerals (sepiolite and palygorskite) has been a widely studied for improving their surface and catalytic properties - so they all should work to a degree.  used to remove contaminants like surfactants and additives from kerosene, diesel, and other fuel oils [[http://jaxonfiltration.com/|#]] 
